commitResults.messageBody:
- Changed bot name from Duke to SwitchBlade
- Added echoing functionality, bot quits when user types "bye"

- Stopped using echo function, moved echoing to addTask of myList
- myList class created to manage tasks and print all tasks
- myList toString() is overridden to print in the required way

- Added Task class to the bot
- Tasks are no longer maintained as a string in myList, all are managed as an ArrayList

- Minor data input validation to ensure that the /by and /at arguments are properly supplied. Must contain the arguments and must have something after the argument.
- Deadline and myEvent extends Task and overrides toString() method accordingly
- Edited runtest.sh script to exclude dos2unix as it isn't available on my system and is not necessary

- checked for no args after todo being included
- invalid commands have been caught
- Implementation already used ArrayList so this was easily integrated

- Introduce static Ui class to handle system output to user
- Introduce static Storage class to handle File IO
- Altered EXPECTED.txt as issues lied in trailing and leading whitespace
- Save function implemented in Storage class

- Static parser class added to work through string commands
- Datetime class added to replace the use of String datetime

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge Successfully Datetime and Save Function
commitResults.messageBody: - Altered methods to save Datetime objects safely into storage file

- Any system output is moved to Ui class
- SwitchBlade.txt is ignored

- Tested 2 methods across Parser and Ui Test
- Leading and trailing whitespace characters are now removed from the returning string in Parser
Documentation not completed but comments have been written for each class

- Bracketing on if-else statements
- Remove unused dependencies
Chatbot can now find tasks with the specified search term
Tests toString method of Task
Previous versions written on JDK 12 on mistake
Verified to be able to execute run and jUnit tests

- Used JavaFXML frameworks
- SwitchBlade class now functions as a command interpreter mostly
- Output from backend is sent from Ui class

- Window closes in 2 seconds instead of 3
- Profile images have been shrunk

- Removed unnecessary version on javafx
- Changed name in init for Ui
- Added argument checking for delete command

- Ui class was not returning correct String
- Number argument checking for markCompleted in myList class
